"""
Comprehensive Tree Data Structures Implementation
================================================
This module implements various tree data structures with interfaces,
time/space complexity analysis, and extensive functionality.
"""

from abc import ABC, abstractmethod
from typing import Any, List, Optional, Tuple, Dict, Deque
from collections import deque
import random
import time
import math

# =============================================================================
# INTERFACES
# =============================================================================

class TreeInterface(ABC):
    """Abstract base class for all tree implementations"""
    
    @abstractmethod
    def insert(self, value: Any) -> bool:
        """Insert a value into the tree"""
        pass
    
    @abstractmethod
    def search(self, value: Any) -> bool:
        """Search for a value in the tree"""
        pass
    
    @abstractmethod
    def delete(self, value: Any) -> bool:
        """Delete a value from the tree"""
        pass
    
    @abstractmethod
    def get_height(self) -> int:
        """Get the height of the tree"""
        pass
    
    @abstractmethod
    def get_size(self) -> int:
        """Get the number of nodes in the tree"""
        pass
    
    @abstractmethod
    def traverse_inorder(self) -> List[Any]:
        """Inorder traversal of the tree"""
        pass
    
    @abstractmethod
    def traverse_preorder(self) -> List[Any]:
        """Preorder traversal of the tree"""
        pass
    
    @abstractmethod
    def traverse_postorder(self) -> List[Any]:
        """Postorder traversal of the tree"""
        pass
    
    @abstractmethod
    def find_min(self) -> Any:
        """Find minimum value in the tree"""
        pass
    
    @abstractmethod
    def find_max(self) -> Any:
        """Find maximum value in the tree"""
        pass

class BalancedTreeInterface(TreeInterface):
    """Interface for balanced trees with additional balancing operations"""
    
    @abstractmethod
    def is_balanced(self) -> bool:
        """Check if the tree is balanced"""
        pass
    
    @abstractmethod
    def balance_tree(self) -> None:
        """Balance the tree"""
        pass

# =============================================================================
# BINARY SEARCH TREE IMPLEMENTATION
# =============================================================================

class BSTNode:
    """Node class for Binary Search Tree"""
    
    def __init__(self, value: Any):
        self.value = value
        self.left: Optional['BSTNode'] = None
        self.right: Optional['BSTNode'] = None
        self.parent: Optional['BSTNode'] = None
        
    def __str__(self):
        return f"BSTNode({self.value})"

class BinarySearchTree(TreeInterface):
    """
    Binary Search Tree Implementation
    Time Complexity:
        - Insert: O(h) where h is height, O(log n) average, O(n) worst
        - Search: O(h) where h is height, O(log n) average, O(n) worst  
        - Delete: O(h) where h is height, O(log n) average, O(n) worst
        - Traversal: O(n) for all traversals
    Space Complexity: O(n) for storing n nodes
    """
    
    def __init__(self):
        self.root: Optional[BSTNode] = None
        self._size = 0
        self.operations_count = 0
        
    def insert(self, value: Any) -> bool:
        """Insert a value into BST - Time: O(h), Space: O(1)"""
        self.operations_count += 1
        
        if self.root is None:
            self.root = BSTNode(value)
            self._size += 1
            return True
            
        return self._insert_recursive(self.root, value)
    
    def _insert_recursive(self, node: BSTNode, value: Any) -> bool:
        """Recursive helper for insertion"""
        if value == node.value:
            return False  # Duplicate values not allowed
            
        if value < node.value:
            if node.left is None:
                node.left = BSTNode(value)
                node.left.parent = node
                self._size += 1
                return True
            else:
                return self._insert_recursive(node.left, value)
        else:
            if node.right is None:
                node.right = BSTNode(value)
                node.right.parent = node
                self._size += 1
                return True
            else:
                return self._insert_recursive(node.right, value)
    
    def search(self, value: Any) -> bool:
        """Search for value in BST - Time: O(h), Space: O(1)"""
        self.operations_count += 1
        return self._search_recursive(self.root, value)
    
    def _search_recursive(self, node: Optional[BSTNode], value: Any) -> bool:
        """Recursive helper for search"""
        if node is None:
            return False
            
        if value == node.value:
            return True
        elif value < node.value:
            return self._search_recursive(node.left, value)
        else:
            return self._search_recursive(node.right, value)
    
    def delete(self, value: Any) -> bool:
        """Delete value from BST - Time: O(h), Space: O(1)"""
        self.operations_count += 1
        node_to_delete = self._find_node(self.root, value)
        
        if node_to_delete is None:
            return False
            
        self._delete_node(node_to_delete)
        self._size -= 1
        return True
    
    def _find_node(self, node: Optional[BSTNode], value: Any) -> Optional[BSTNode]:
        """Find node with given value"""
        if node is None:
            return None
            
        if value == node.value:
            return node
        elif value < node.value:
            return self._find_node(node.left, value)
        else:
            return self._find_node(node.right, value)
    
    def _delete_node(self, node: BSTNode) -> None:
        """Delete a node from BST"""
        # Case 1: Node has no children
        if node.left is None and node.right is None:
            self._transplant(node, None)
            
        # Case 2: Node has only right child
        elif node.left is None:
            self._transplant(node, node.right)
            
        # Case 3: Node has only left child
        elif node.right is None:
            self._transplant(node, node.left)
            
        # Case 4: Node has two children
        else:
            successor = self._find_min_node(node.right)
            if successor.parent != node:
                self._transplant(successor, successor.right)
                successor.right = node.right
                successor.right.parent = successor
                
            self._transplant(node, successor)
            successor.left = node.left
            successor.left.parent = successor
    
    def _transplant(self, u: BSTNode, v: Optional[BSTNode]) -> None:
        """Replace subtree rooted at u with subtree rooted at v"""
        if u.parent is None:
            self.root = v
        elif u == u.parent.left:
            u.parent.left = v
        else:
            u.parent.right = v
            
        if v is not None:
            v.parent = u.parent
    
    def _find_min_node(self, node: BSTNode) -> BSTNode:
        """Find node with minimum value in subtree"""
        while node.left is not None:
            node = node.left
        return node
    
    def get_height(self) -> int:
        """Get tree height - Time: O(n), Space: O(h)"""
        return self._calculate_height(self.root)
    
    def _calculate_height(self, node: Optional[BSTNode]) -> int:
        """Calculate height recursively"""
        if node is None:
            return 0
        return 1 + max(self._calculate_height(node.left), 
                      self._calculate_height(node.right))
    
    def get_size(self) -> int:
        """Get number of nodes - Time: O(1), Space: O(1)"""
        return self._size
    
    def traverse_inorder(self) -> List[Any]:
        """Inorder traversal - Time: O(n), Space: O(h)"""
        result = []
        self._inorder_recursive(self.root, result)
        return result
    
    def _inorder_recursive(self, node: Optional[BSTNode], result: List[Any]) -> None:
        """Recursive inorder traversal"""
        if node is not None:
            self._inorder_recursive(node.left, result)
            result.append(node.value)
            self._inorder_recursive(node.right, result)
    
    def traverse_preorder(self) -> List[Any]:
        """Preorder traversal - Time: O(n), Space: O(h)"""
        result = []
        self._preorder_recursive(self.root, result)
        return result
    
    def _preorder_recursive(self, node: Optional[BSTNode], result: List[Any]) -> None:
        """Recursive preorder traversal"""
        if node is not None:
            result.append(node.value)
            self._preorder_recursive(node.left, result)
            self._preorder_recursive(node.right, result)
    
    def traverse_postorder(self) -> List[Any]:
        """Postorder traversal - Time: O(n), Space: O(h)"""
        result = []
        self._postorder_recursive(self.root, result)
        return result
    
    def _postorder_recursive(self, node: Optional[BSTNode], result: List[Any]) -> None:
        """Recursive postorder traversal"""
        if node is not None:
            self._postorder_recursive(node.left, result)
            self._postorder_recursive(node.right, result)
            result.append(node.value)
    
    def traverse_level_order(self) -> List[Any]:
        """Level order traversal - Time: O(n), Space: O(n)"""
        if self.root is None:
            return []
            
        result = []
        queue = deque([self.root])
        
        while queue:
            node = queue.popleft()
            result.append(node.value)
            
            if node.left:
                queue.append(node.left)
            if node.right:
                queue.append(node.right)
                
        return result
    
    def find_min(self) -> Any:
        """Find minimum value - Time: O(h), Space: O(1)"""
        if self.root is None:
            return None
            
        current = self.root
        while current.left is not None:
            current = current.left
        return current.value
    
    def find_max(self) -> Any:
        """Find maximum value - Time: O(h), Space: O(1)"""
        if self.root is None:
            return None
            
        current = self.root
        while current.right is not None:
            current = current.right
        return current.value
    
    def is_valid_bst(self) -> bool:
        """Check if tree is valid BST - Time: O(n), Space: O(h)"""
        return self._is_valid_recursive(self.root, float('-inf'), float('inf'))
    
    def _is_valid_recursive(self, node: Optional[BSTNode], min_val: float, max_val: float) -> bool:
        """Recursive helper for BST validation"""
        if node is None:
            return True
            
        if not (min_val < node.value < max_val):
            return False
            
        return (self._is_valid_recursive(node.left, min_val, node.value) and
                self._is_valid_recursive(node.right, node.value, max_val))
    
    def get_successor(self, value: Any) -> Any:
        """Find inorder successor - Time: O(h), Space: O(1)"""
        node = self._find_node(self.root, value)
        if node is None:
            return None
            
        # Case 1: Node has right subtree
        if node.right is not None:
            return self._find_min_node(node.right).value
            
        # Case 2: No right subtree
        ancestor = node.parent
        while ancestor is not None and node == ancestor.right:
            node = ancestor
            ancestor = ancestor.parent
        return ancestor.value if ancestor else None
    
    def get_predecessor(self, value: Any) -> Any:
        """Find inorder predecessor - Time: O(h), Space: O(1)"""
        node = self._find_node(self.root, value)
        if node is None:
            return None
            
        # Case 1: Node has left subtree
        if node.left is not None:
            return self._find_max_node(node.left).value
            
        # Case 2: No left subtree
        ancestor = node.parent
        while ancestor is not None and node == ancestor.left:
            node = ancestor
            ancestor = ancestor.parent
        return ancestor.value if ancestor else None
    
    def _find_max_node(self, node: BSTNode) -> BSTNode:
        """Find node with maximum value in subtree"""
        while node.right is not None:
            node = node.right
        return node
    
    def get_operations_count(self) -> int:
        """Get total operations performed"""
        return self.operations_count
    
    def clear_operations_count(self) -> None:
        """Reset operations counter"""
        self.operations_count = 0

# =============================================================================
# AVL TREE IMPLEMENTATION (Self-Balancing BST)
# =============================================================================

class AVLNode:
    """Node class for AVL Tree"""
    
    def __init__(self, value: Any):
        self.value = value
        self.left: Optional['AVLNode'] = None
        self.right: Optional['AVLNode'] = None
        self.height = 1
        self.balance_factor = 0
        
    def __str__(self):
        return f"AVLNode({self.value}, h={self.height})"

class AVLTree(BalancedTreeInterface):
    """
    AVL Tree Implementation (Self-Balancing Binary Search Tree)
    Time Complexity:
        - Insert: O(log n) guaranteed
        - Search: O(log n) guaranteed  
        - Delete: O(log n) guaranteed
        - Rotations: O(1)
    Space Complexity: O(n) for storing n nodes
    """
    
    def __init__(self):
        self.root: Optional[AVLNode] = None
        self._size = 0
        self.rotations_count = 0
        
    def insert(self, value: Any) -> bool:
        """Insert value into AVL tree - Time: O(log n), Space: O(log n)"""
        if self.root is None:
            self.root = AVLNode(value)
            self._size += 1
            return True
            
        self.root, inserted = self._insert_recursive(self.root, value)
        if inserted:
            self._size += 1
        return inserted
    
    def _insert_recursive(self, node: AVLNode, value: Any) -> Tuple[AVLNode, bool]:
        """Recursive insertion with balancing"""
        if value == node.value:
            return node, False  # Duplicate
            
        if value < node.value:
            if node.left is None:
                node.left = AVLNode(value)
            else:
                node.left, inserted = self._insert_recursive(node.left, value)
                if not inserted:
                    return node, False
        else:
            if node.right is None:
                node.right = AVLNode(value)
            else:
                node.right, inserted = self._insert_recursive(node.right, value)
                if not inserted:
                    return node, False
                    
        # Update height and balance factor
        self._update_height(node)
        
        # Balance the tree
        return self._balance_node(node), True
    
    def _update_height(self, node: AVLNode) -> None:
        """Update height and balance factor of node"""
        left_height = node.left.height if node.left else 0
        right_height = node.right.height if node.right else 0
        
        node.height = 1 + max(left_height, right_height)
        node.balance_factor = left_height - right_height
    
    def _balance_node(self, node: AVLNode) -> AVLNode:
        """Balance the node and return new root of subtree"""
        # Left heavy
        if node.balance_factor > 1:
            # Left-Right case
            if node.left and node.left.balance_factor < 0:
                node.left = self._rotate_left(node.left)
                self.rotations_count += 1
            # Left-Left case
            node = self._rotate_right(node)
            self.rotations_count += 1
            
        # Right heavy  
        elif node.balance_factor < -1:
            # Right-Left case
            if node.right and node.right.balance_factor > 0:
                node.right = self._rotate_right(node.right)
                self.rotations_count += 1
            # Right-Right case
            node = self._rotate_left(node)
            self.rotations_count += 1
            
        return node
    
    def _rotate_left(self, z: AVLNode) -> AVLNode:
        """Left rotation"""
        y = z.right
        T2 = y.left
        
        # Perform rotation
        y.left = z
        z.right = T2
        
        # Update heights
        self._update_height(z)
        self._update_height(y)
        
        return y
    
    def _rotate_right(self, z: AVLNode) -> AVLNode:
        """Right rotation"""
        y = z.left
        T3 = y.right
        
        # Perform rotation
        y.right = z
        z.left = T3
        
        # Update heights
        self._update_height(z)
        self._update_height(y)
        
        return y
    
    def search(self, value: Any) -> bool:
        """Search for value in AVL tree - Time: O(log n), Space: O(log n)"""
        return self._search_recursive(self.root, value)
    
    def _search_recursive(self, node: Optional[AVLNode], value: Any) -> bool:
        """Recursive search"""
        if node is None:
            return False
            
        if value == node.value:
            return True
        elif value < node.value:
            return self._search_recursive(node.left, value)
        else:
            return self._search_recursive(node.right, value)
    
    def delete(self, value: Any) -> bool:
        """Delete value from AVL tree - Time: O(log n), Space: O(log n)"""
        if self.root is None:
            return False
            
        self.root, deleted = self._delete_recursive(self.root, value)
        if deleted:
            self._size -= 1
        return deleted
    
    def _delete_recursive(self, node: AVLNode, value: Any) -> Tuple[Optional[AVLNode], bool]:
        """Recursive deletion with balancing"""
        if value < node.value:
            if node.left is None:
                return node, False
            node.left, deleted = self._delete_recursive(node.left, value)
            if not deleted:
                return node, False
                
        elif value > node.value:
            if node.right is None:
                return node, False
            node.right, deleted = self._delete_recursive(node.right, value)
            if not deleted:
                return node, False
                
        else:  # Found node to delete
            # Node with only one child or no child
            if node.left is None:
                return node.right, True
            elif node.right is None:
                return node.left, True
                
            # Node with two children: get inorder successor
            temp = self._find_min_node(node.right)
            node.value = temp.value
            node.right, _ = self._delete_recursive(node.right, temp.value)
            deleted = True
            
        # Update height and balance
        self._update_height(node)
        return self._balance_node(node), True
    
    def _find_min_node(self, node: AVLNode) -> AVLNode:
        """Find node with minimum value"""
        while node.left is not None:
            node = node.left
        return node
    
    def get_height(self) -> int:
        """Get tree height - Time: O(1), Space: O(1)"""
        return self.root.height if self.root else 0
    
    def get_size(self) -> int:
        """Get number of nodes - Time: O(1), Space: O(1)"""
        return self._size
    
    def traverse_inorder(self) -> List[Any]:
        """Inorder traversal - Time: O(n), Space: O(h)"""
        result = []
        self._inorder_recursive(self.root, result)
        return result
    
    def _inorder_recursive(self, node: Optional[AVLNode], result: List[Any]) -> None:
        """Recursive inorder traversal"""
        if node is not None:
            self._inorder_recursive(node.left, result)
            result.append(node.value)
            self._inorder_recursive(node.right, result)
    
    def traverse_preorder(self) -> List[Any]:
        """Preorder traversal - Time: O(n), Space: O(h)"""
        result = []
        self._preorder_recursive(self.root, result)
        return result
    
    def _preorder_recursive(self, node: Optional[AVLNode], result: List[Any]) -> None:
        """Recursive preorder traversal"""
        if node is not None:
            result.append(node.value)
            self._preorder_recursive(node.left, result)
            self._preorder_recursive(node.right, result)
    
    def traverse_postorder(self) -> List[Any]:
        """Postorder traversal - Time: O(n), Space: O(h)"""
        result = []
        self._postorder_recursive(self.root, result)
        return result
    
    def _postorder_recursive(self, node: Optional[AVLNode], result: List[Any]) -> None:
        """Recursive postorder traversal"""
        if node is not None:
            self._postorder_recursive(node.left, result)
            self._postorder_recursive(node.right, result)
            result.append(node.value)
    
    def find_min(self) -> Any:
        """Find minimum value - Time: O(log n), Space: O(1)"""
        if self.root is None:
            return None
            
        current = self.root
        while current.left is not None:
            current = current.left
        return current.value
    
    def find_max(self) -> Any:
        """Find maximum value - Time: O(log n), Space: O(1)"""
        if self.root is None:
            return None
            
        current = self.root
        while current.right is not None:
            current = current.right
        return current.value
    
    def is_balanced(self) -> bool:
        """Check if tree is balanced - Time: O(n), Space: O(h)"""
        return self._check_balanced(self.root)
    
    def _check_balanced(self, node: Optional[AVLNode]) -> bool:
        """Recursive balance check"""
        if node is None:
            return True
            
        left_height = node.left.height if node.left else 0
        right_height = node.right.height if node.right else 0
        
        if abs(left_height - right_height) > 1:
            return False
            
        return self._check_balanced(node.left) and self._check_balanced(node.right)
    
    def balance_tree(self) -> None:
        """Balance the tree - AVL trees are always balanced by design"""
        pass  # AVL trees maintain balance automatically
    
    def get_rotations_count(self) -> int:
        """Get number of rotations performed"""
        return self.rotations_count

# =============================================================================
# RED-BLACK TREE IMPLEMENTATION
# =============================================================================

class Color:
    RED = 0
    BLACK = 1

class RBNode:
    """Node class for Red-Black Tree"""
    
    def __init__(self, value: Any):
        self.value = value
        self.left: Optional['RBNode'] = None
        self.right: Optional['RBNode'] = None
        self.parent: Optional['RBNode'] = None
        self.color = Color.RED  # New nodes are always red
        
    def __str__(self):
        color_str = "RED" if self.color == Color.RED else "BLACK"
        return f"RBNode({self.value}, {color_str})"

class RedBlackTree(BalancedTreeInterface):
    """
    Red-Black Tree Implementation (Self-Balancing Binary Search Tree)
    Time Complexity:
        - Insert: O(log n) guaranteed
        - Search: O(log n) guaranteed
        - Delete: O(log n) guaranteed  
        - Rotations: O(1)
    Space Complexity: O(n) for storing n nodes
    """
    
    def __init__(self):
        self.nil = RBNode(None)  Sentinel node
        self.nil.color = Color.BLACK
        self.root = self.nil
        self._size = 0
        self.rotations_count = 0
        
    def insert(self, value: Any) -> bool:
        """Insert value into Red-Black tree - Time: O(log n), Space: O(1)"""
        new_node = RBNode(value)
        new_node.left = self.nil
        new_node.right = self.nil
        
        # Regular BST insertion
        parent = None
        current = self.root
        
        while current != self.nil:
            parent = current
            if value < current.value:
                current = current.left
            elif value > current.value:
                current = current.right
            else:
                return False  # Duplicate
                
        # Set parent
        new_node.parent = parent
        
        if parent is None:
            self.root = new_node
        elif value < parent.value:
            parent.left = new_node
        else:
            parent.right = new_node
            
        self._size += 1
        
        # Fix Red-Black properties
        self._insert_fixup(new_node)
        return True
    
    def _insert_fixup(self, node: RBNode) -> None:
        """Fix Red-Black tree properties after insertion"""
        while node.parent and node.parent.color == Color.RED:
            if node.parent == node.parent.parent.left:
                uncle = node.parent.parent.right
                
                # Case 1: Uncle is red
                if uncle.color == Color.RED:
                    node.parent.color = Color.BLACK
                    uncle.color = Color.BLACK
                    node.parent.parent.color = Color.RED
                    node = node.parent.parent
                else:
                    # Case 2: Node is right child
                    if node == node.parent.right:
                        node = node.parent
                        self._left_rotate(node)
                        self.rotations_count += 1
                    
                    # Case 3: Node is left child
                    node.parent.color = Color.BLACK
                    node.parent.parent.color = Color.RED
                    self._right_rotate(node.parent.parent)
                    self.rotations_count += 1
            else:
                uncle = node.parent.parent.left
                
                # Case 1: Uncle is red
                if uncle.color == Color.RED:
                    node.parent.color = Color.BLACK
                    uncle.color = Color.BLACK
                    node.parent.parent.color = Color.RED
                    node = node.parent.parent
                else:
                    # Case 2: Node is left child
                    if node == node.parent.left:
                        node = node.parent
                        self._right_rotate(node)
                        self.rotations_count += 1
                    
                    # Case 3: Node is right child
                    node.parent.color = Color.BLACK
                    node.parent.parent.color = Color.RED
                    self._left_rotate(node.parent.parent)
                    self.rotations_count += 1
                    
            if node == self.root:
                break
                
        self.root.color = Color.BLACK
    
    def _left_rotate(self, x: RBNode) -> None:
        """Left rotation"""
        y = x.right
        x.right = y.left
        
        if y.left != self.nil:
            y.left.parent = x
            
        y.parent = x.parent
        
        if x.parent is None:
            self.root = y
        elif x == x.parent.left:
            x.parent.left = y
        else:
            x.parent.right = y
            
        y.left = x
        x.parent = y
    
    def _right_rotate(self, y: RBNode) -> None:
        """Right rotation"""
        x = y.left
        y.left = x.right
        
        if x.right != self.nil:
            x.right.parent = y
            
        x.parent = y.parent
        
        if y.parent is None:
            self.root = x
        elif y == y.parent.right:
            y.parent.right = x
        else:
            y.parent.left = x
            
        x.right = y
        y.parent = x
    
    def search(self, value: Any) -> bool:
        """Search for value in Red-Black tree - Time: O(log n), Space: O(1)"""
        current = self.root
        
        while current != self.nil:
            if value == current.value:
                return True
            elif value < current.value:
                current = current.left
            else:
                current = current.right
                
        return False
    
    def delete(self, value: Any) -> bool:
        """Delete value from Red-Black tree - Time: O(log n), Space: O(1)"""
        node = self._find_node(value)
        if node == self.nil:
            return False
            
        self._delete_node(node)
        self._size -= 1
        return True
    
    def _find_node(self, value: Any) -> RBNode:
        """Find node with given value"""
        current = self.root
        
        while current != self.nil:
            if value == current.value:
                return current
            elif value < current.value:
                current = current.left
            else:
                current = current.right
                
        return self.nil
    
    def _delete_node(self, z: RBNode) -> None:
        """Delete node from Red-Black tree"""
        y = z
        y_original_color = y.color
        x = None
        
        if z.left == self.nil:
            x = z.right
            self._transplant(z, z.right)
        elif z.right == self.nil:
            x = z.left
            self._transplant(z, z.left)
        else:
            y = self._find_min_node(z.right)
            y_original_color = y.color
            x = y.right
            
            if y.parent == z:
                if x != self.nil:
                    x.parent = y
            else:
                self._transplant(y, y.right)
                y.right = z.right
                y.right.parent = y
                
            self._transplant(z, y)
            y.left = z.left
            y.left.parent = y
            y.color = z.color
            
        if y_original_color == Color.BLACK:
            self._delete_fixup(x)
    
    def _transplant(self, u: RBNode, v: RBNode) -> None:
        """Replace subtree rooted at u with subtree rooted at v"""
        if u.parent is None:
            self.root = v
        elif u == u.parent.left:
            u.parent.left = v
        else:
            u.parent.right = v
            
        v.parent = u.parent
    
    def _find_min_node(self, node: RBNode) -> RBNode:
        """Find node with minimum value"""
        while node.left != self.nil:
            node = node.left
        return node
    
    def _delete_fixup(self, x: RBNode) -> None:
        """Fix Red-Black properties after deletion"""
        while x != self.root and x.color == Color.BLACK:
            if x == x.parent.left:
                w = x.parent.right
                
                # Case 1: Sibling is red
                if w.color == Color.RED:
                    w.color = Color.BLACK
                    x.parent.color = Color.RED
                    self._left_rotate(x.parent)
                    self.rotations_count += 1
                    w = x.parent.right
                
                # Case 2: Both sibling's children are black
                if w.left.color == Color.BLACK and w.right.color == Color.BLACK:
                    w.color = Color.RED
                    x = x.parent
                else:
                    # Case 3: Sibling's right child is black
                    if w.right.color == Color.BLACK:
                        w.left.color = Color.BLACK
                        w.color = Color.RED
                        self._right_rotate(w)
                        self.rotations_count += 1
                        w = x.parent.right
                    
                    # Case 4: Sibling's right child is red
                    w.color = x.parent.color
                    x.parent.color = Color.BLACK
                    w.right.color = Color.BLACK
                    self._left_rotate(x.parent)
                    self.rotations_count += 1
                    x = self.root
            else:
                w = x.parent.left
                
                # Case 1: Sibling is red
                if w.color == Color.RED:
                    w.color = Color.BLACK
                    x.parent.color = Color.RED
                    self._right_rotate(x.parent)
                    self.rotations_count += 1
                    w = x.parent.left
                
                # Case 2: Both sibling's children are black
                if w.right.color == Color.BLACK and w.left.color == Color.BLACK:
                    w.color = Color.RED
                    x = x.parent
                else:
                    # Case 3: Sibling's left child is black
                    if w.left.color == Color.BLACK:
                        w.right.color = Color.BLACK
                        w.color = Color.RED
                        self._left_rotate(w)
                        self.rotations_count += 1
                        w = x.parent.left
                    
                    # Case 4: Sibling's left child is red
                    w.color = x.parent.color
                    x.parent.color = Color.BLACK
                    w.left.color = Color.BLACK
                    self._right_rotate(x.parent)
                    self.rotations_count += 1
                    x = self.root
                    
        x.color = Color.BLACK
    
    def get_height(self) -> int:
        """Get tree height - Time: O(n), Space: O(h)"""
        return self._calculate_height(self.root)
    
    def _calculate_height(self, node: RBNode) -> int:
        """Calculate height recursively"""
        if node == self.nil:
            return 0
        return 1 + max(self._calculate_height(node.left), 
                      self._calculate_height(node.right))
    
    def get_size(self) -> int:
        """Get number of nodes - Time: O(1), Space: O(1)"""
        return self._size
    
    def traverse_inorder(self) -> List[Any]:
        """Inorder traversal - Time: O(n), Space: O(h)"""
        result = []
        self._inorder_recursive(self.root, result)
        return result
    
    def _inorder_recursive(self, node: RBNode, result: List[Any]) -> None:
        """Recursive inorder traversal"""
        if node != self.nil:
            self._inorder_recursive(node.left, result)
            result.append(node.value)
            self._inorder_recursive(node.right, result)
    
    def traverse_preorder(self) -> List[Any]:
        """Preorder traversal - Time: O(n), Space: O(h)"""
        result = []
        self._preorder_recursive(self.root, result)
        return result
    
    def _preorder_recursive(self, node: RBNode, result: List[Any]) -> None:
        """Recursive preorder traversal"""
        if node != self.nil:
            result.append(node.value)
            self._preorder_recursive(node.left, result)
            self._preorder_recursive(node.right, result)
    
    def traverse_postorder(self) -> List[Any]:
        """Postorder traversal - Time: O(n), Space: O(h)"""
        result = []
        self._postorder_recursive(self.root, result)
        return result
    
    def _postorder_recursive(self, node: RBNode, result: List[Any]) -> None:
        """Recursive postorder traversal"""
        if node != self.nil:
            self._postorder_recursive(node.left, result)
            self._postorder_recursive(node.right, result)
            result.append(node.value)
    
    def find_min(self) -> Any:
        """Find minimum value - Time: O(log n), Space: O(1)"""
        if self.root == self.nil:
            return None
            
        current = self.root
        while current.left != self.nil:
            current = current.left
        return current.value
    
    def find_max(self) -> Any:
        """Find maximum value - Time: O(log n), Space: O(1)"""
        if self.root == self.nil:
            return None
            
        current = self.root
        while current.right != self.nil:
            current = current.right
        return current.value
    
    def is_balanced(self) -> bool:
        """Check if tree is balanced - Time: O(n), Space: O(h)"""
        return self._check_balanced(self.root)
    
    def _check_balanced(self, node: RBNode) -> bool:
        """Recursive balance check"""
        if node == self.nil:
            return True
            
        left_height = self._calculate_height(node.left)
        right_height = self._calculate_height(node.right)
        
        if abs(left_height - right_height) > 1:
            return False
            
        return self._check_balanced(node.left) and self._check_balanced(node.right)
    
    def balance_tree(self) -> None:
        """Balance the tree - Red-Black trees are always balanced by design"""
        pass  # Red-Black trees maintain balance automatically
    
    def get_rotations_count(self) -> int:
        """Get number of rotations performed"""
        return self.rotations_count
    
    def validate_rb_properties(self) -> bool:
        """Validate all Red-Black tree properties"""
        return (self._validate_root_is_black() and
                self._validate_red_nodes_have_black_children() and
                self._validate_black_height_same())
    
    def _validate_root_is_black(self) -> bool:
        """Validate root is black"""
        return self.root.color == Color.BLACK
    
    def _validate_red_nodes_have_black_children(self) -> bool:
        """Validate all red nodes have black children"""
        return self._validate_red_children_recursive(self.root)
    
    def _validate_red_children_recursive(self, node: RBNode) -> bool:
        """Recursive helper for red children validation"""
        if node == self.nil:
            return True
            
        if node.color == Color.RED:
            if node.left.color == Color.RED or node.right.color == Color.RED:
                return False
                
        return (self._validate_red_children_recursive(node.left) and
                self._validate_red_children_recursive(node.right))
    
    def _validate_black_height_same(self) -> bool:
        """Validate black height is same for all paths"""
        if self.root == self.nil:
            return True
            
        black_height = None
        stack = [(self.root, 0)]  # (node, current_black_height)
        
        while stack:
            node, current_bh = stack.pop()
            
            if node == self.nil:
                if black_height is None:
                    black_height = current_bh
                elif current_bh != black_height:
                    return False
                continue
                
            # Add black height if node is black
            next_bh = current_bh + (1 if node.color == Color.BLACK else 0)
            stack.append((node.left, next_bh))
            stack.append((node.right, next_bh))
            
        return True

# =============================================================================
# B-TREE IMPLEMENTATION
# =============================================================================

class BTreeNode:
    """Node class for B-Tree"""
    
    def __init__(self, t: int, leaf: bool = False):
        self.t = t  # Minimum degree
        self.leaf = leaf
        self.keys: List[Any] = []
        self.children: List['BTreeNode'] = []
        self.n = 0  # Current number of keys
        
    def __str__(self):
        return f"BTreeNode(keys={self.keys}, leaf={self.leaf})"

class BTree(TreeInterface):
    """
    B-Tree Implementation (Balanced multi-way search tree)
    Time Complexity:
        - Insert: O(t * log_t n)
        - Search: O(t * log_t n) 
        - Delete: O(t * log_t n)
        - Split: O(t)
    Space Complexity: O(n) for storing n keys
    """
    
    def __init__(self, t: int = 3):
        """
        Initialize B-Tree
        Args:
            t: Minimum degree (defines the range for number of keys)
        """
        self.root: Optional[BTreeNode] = None
        self.t = t  # Minimum degree
        self._size = 0
        
    def insert(self, value: Any) -> bool:
        """Insert value into B-Tree - Time: O(t * log_t n), Space: O(t * log_t n)"""
        if self.root is None:
            self.root = BTreeNode(self.t, True)
            self.root.keys.append(value)
            self.root.n = 1
            self._size += 1
            return True
            
        # If root is full, then tree grows in height
        if self.root.n == 2 * self.t - 1:
            # Create new root
            new_root = BTreeNode(self.t, False)
            new_root.children.append(self.root)
            
            # Split the old root
            self._split_child(new_root, 0)
            
            # New root has two children now, decide which one will have new key
            i = 0
            if new_root.keys[0] < value:
                i += 1
            self._insert_non_full(new_root.children[i], value)
            
            self.root = new_root
        else:
            self._insert_non_full(self.root, value)
            
        self._size += 1
        return True
    
    def _insert_non_full(self, node: BTreeNode, value: Any) -> None:
        """Insert into non-full node"""
        i = node.n - 1
        
        if node.leaf:
            # Insert into leaf node
            node.keys.append(None)  # Make space
            while i >= 0 and node.keys[i] > value:
                node.keys[i + 1] = node.keys[i]
                i -= 1
            node.keys[i + 1] = value
            node.n += 1
        else:
            # Find child which will have the new key
            while i >= 0 and node.keys[i] > value:
                i -= 1
            i += 1
            
            # Check if child is full
            if node.children[i].n == 2 * self.t - 1:
                self._split_child(node, i)
                
                # After split, the middle key of node.children[i] goes up
                if node.keys[i] < value:
                    i += 1
                    
            self._insert_non_full(node.children[i], value)
    
    def _split_child(self, parent: BTreeNode, i: int) -> None:
        """Split the child node"""
        t = self.t
        y = parent.children[i]  # Child to split
        z = BTreeNode(t, y.leaf)
        
        # Create new node z
        z.n = t - 1
        
        # Copy the last (t-1) keys of y to z
        z.keys = y.keys[t:(2 * t - 1)]
        
        # Copy the last t children of y to z if not leaf
        if not y.leaf:
            z.children = y.children[t:(2 * t)]
            
        # Reduce number of keys in y
        y.n = t - 1
        
        # Create space for new child in parent
        parent.children.insert(i + 1, z)
        
        # A key of y will move to parent
        parent.keys.insert(i, y.keys[t - 1])
        
        # Update parent's key count
        parent.n += 1
    
    def search(self, value: Any) -> bool:
        """Search for value in B-Tree - Time: O(t * log_t n), Space: O(log_t n)"""
        return self._search_recursive(self.root, value) is not None
    
    def _search_recursive(self, node: Optional[BTreeNode], value: Any) -> Optional[BTreeNode]:
        """Recursive search in B-Tree"""
        if node is None:
            return None
            
        i = 0
        while i < node.n and value > node.keys[i]:
            i += 1
            
        if i < node.n and value == node.keys[i]:
            return node
            
        if node.leaf:
            return None
            
        return self._search_recursive(node.children[i], value)
    
    def delete(self, value: Any) -> bool:
        """Delete value from B-Tree - Time: O(t * log_t n), Space: O(t * log_t n)"""
        if self.root is None:
            return False
            
        result = self._delete_recursive(self.root, value)
        if result:
            self._size -= 1
            
            # If root has 0 keys, make its first child as new root
            if self.root.n == 0:
                if self.root.leaf:
                    self.root = None
                else:
                    self.root = self.root.children[0]
                    
        return result
    
    def _delete_recursive(self, node: BTreeNode, value: Any) -> bool:
        """Recursive deletion from B-Tree"""
        idx = self._find_key_index(node, value)
        
        if idx < node.n and node.keys[idx] == value:
            # Key found in this node
            if node.leaf:
                self._remove_from_leaf(node, idx)
            else:
                self._remove_from_non_leaf(node, idx)
            return True
        else:
            if node.leaf:
                return False  # Key not found
                
            # Key is in subtree rooted with this node
            flag = (idx == node.n)  # True if last child
            
            # If child has less than t keys, fill it
            if node.children[idx].n < self.t:
                self._fill_child(node, idx)
                
            # If last child was merged, it must have merged with previous child
            if flag and idx > node.n:
                return self._delete_recursive(node.children[idx - 1], value)
            else:
                return self._delete_recursive(node.children[idx], value)
    
    def _find_key_index(self, node: BTreeNode, value: Any) -> int:
        """Find index of key in node"""
        idx = 0
        while idx < node.n and node.keys[idx] < value:
            idx += 1
        return idx
    
    def _remove_from_leaf(self, node: BTreeNode, idx: int) -> None:
        """Remove key from leaf node"""
        node.keys.pop(idx)
        node.n -= 1
    
    def _remove_from_non_leaf(self, node: BTreeNode, idx: int) -> None:
        """Remove key from non-leaf node"""
        key = node.keys[idx]
        
        # If predecessor child has at least t keys
        if node.children[idx].n >= self.t:
            pred = self._get_predecessor(node, idx)
            node.keys[idx] = pred
            self._delete_recursive(node.children[idx], pred)
            
        # If successor child has at least t keys  
        elif node.children[idx + 1].n >= self.t:
            succ = self._get_successor(node, idx)
            node.keys[idx] = succ
            self._delete_recursive(node.children[idx + 1], succ)
            
        # Both children have t-1 keys, merge them
        else:
            self._merge_children(node, idx)
            self._delete_recursive(node.children[idx], key)
    
    def _get_predecessor(self, node: BTreeNode, idx: int) -> Any:
        """Get predecessor of key at index idx"""
        current = node.children[idx]
        while not current.leaf:
            current = current.children[current.n]
        return current.keys[current.n - 1]
    
    def _get_successor(self, node: BTreeNode, idx: int) -> Any:
        """Get successor of key at index idx"""
        current = node.children[idx + 1]
        while not current.leaf:
            current = current.children[0]
        return current.keys[0]
    
    def _fill_child(self, parent: BTreeNode, idx: int) -> None:
        """Fill child that has less than t keys"""
        # Borrow from previous sibling if possible
        if idx != 0 and parent.children[idx - 1].n >= self.t:
            self._borrow_from_prev(parent, idx)
            
        # Borrow from next sibling if possible
        elif idx != parent.n and parent.children[idx + 1].n >= self.t:
            self._borrow_from_next(parent, idx)
            
        # Merge with sibling
        else:
            if idx != parent.n:
                self._merge_children(parent, idx)
            else:
                self._merge_children(parent, idx - 1)
    
    def _borrow_from_prev(self, parent: BTreeNode, idx: int) -> None:
        """Borrow key from previous child"""
        child = parent.children[idx]
        sibling = parent.children[idx - 1]
        
        # Move all keys in child one step ahead
        child.keys.insert(0, parent.keys[idx - 1])
        child.n += 1
        
        if not child.leaf:
            child.children.insert(0, sibling.children.pop())
            
        # Move key from sibling to parent
        parent.keys[idx - 1] = sibling.keys.pop()
        sibling.n -= 1
    
    def _borrow_from_next(self, parent: BTreeNode, idx: int) -> None:
        """Borrow key from next child"""
        child = parent.children[idx]
        sibling = parent.children[idx + 1]
        
        # Move key from parent to child
        child.keys.append(parent.keys[idx])
        child.n += 1
        
        if not child.leaf:
            child.children.append(sibling.children.pop(0))
            
        # Move key from sibling to parent
        parent.keys[idx] = sibling.keys.pop(0)
        sibling.n -= 1
    
    def _merge_children(self, parent: BTreeNode, idx: int) -> None:
        """Merge child[idx] with child[idx+1]"""
        child = parent.children[idx]
        sibling = parent.children[idx + 1]
        
        # Pull key from parent and insert into child
        child.keys.append(parent.keys.pop(idx))
        child.n += 1
        
        # Copy keys from sibling to child
        child.keys.extend(sibling.keys)
        child.n += sibling.n
        
        # Copy children from sibling to child if not leaf
        if not child.leaf:
            child.children.extend(sibling.children)
            
        # Remove sibling from parent
        parent.children.pop(idx + 1)
        parent.n -= 1
    
    def get_height(self) -> int:
        """Get tree height - Time: O(log_t n), Space: O(1)"""
        if self.root is None:
            return 0
            
        height = 0
        current = self.root
        
        while not current.leaf:
            height += 1
            current = current.children[0]
            
        return height + 1
    
    def get_size(self) -> int:
        """Get number of keys - Time: O(1), Space: O(1)"""
        return self._size
    
    def traverse_inorder(self) -> List[Any]:
        """Inorder traversal - Time: O(n), Space: O(log_t n)"""
        result = []
        if self.root:
            self._inorder_recursive(self.root, result)
        return result
    
    def _inorder_recursive(self, node: BTreeNode, result: List[Any]) -> None:
        """Recursive inorder traversal for B-Tree"""
        for i in range(node.n):
            if not node.leaf:
                self._inorder_recursive(node.children[i], result)
            result.append(node.keys[i])
            
        if not node.leaf:
            self._inorder_recursive(node.children[node.n], result)
    
    def traverse_preorder(self) -> List[Any]:
        """Preorder traversal - Time: O(n), Space: O(log_t n)"""
        result = []
        if self.root:
            self._preorder_recursive(self.root, result)
        return result
    
    def _preorder_recursive(self, node: BTreeNode, result: List[Any]) -> None:
        """Recursive preorder traversal for B-Tree"""
        for key in node.keys:
            result.append(key)
            
        if not node.leaf:
            for child in node.children:
                self._preorder_recursive(child, result)
    
    def traverse_postorder(self) -> List[Any]:
        """Postorder traversal - Time: O(n), Space: O(log_t n)"""
        result = []
        if self.root:
            self._postorder_recursive(self.root, result)
        return result
    
    def _postorder_recursive(self, node: BTreeNode, result: List[Any]) -> None:
        """Recursive postorder traversal for B-Tree"""
        if not node.leaf:
            for child in node.children:
                self._postorder_recursive(child, result)
                
        for key in node.keys:
            result.append(key)
    
    def find_min(self) -> Any:
        """Find minimum value - Time: O(log_t n), Space: O(1)"""
        if self.root is None:
            return None
            
        current = self.root
        while not current.leaf:
            current = current.children[0]
            
        return current.keys[0] if current.keys else None
    
    def find_max(self) -> Any:
        """Find maximum value - Time: O(log_t n), Space: O(1)"""
        if self.root is None:
            return None
            
        current = self.root
        while not current.leaf:
            current = current.children[-1]
            
        return current.keys[-1] if current.keys else None
    
    def get_node_count(self) -> int:
        """Get total number of nodes in B-Tree"""
        if self.root is None:
            return 0
            
        count = 0
        stack = [self.root]
        
        while stack:
            node = stack.pop()
            count += 1
            
            if not node.leaf:
                stack.extend(node.children)
                
        return count

class SegmentTree:
    """
    Segment Tree Implementation for Range Queries
    Time Complexity:
        - Build: O(n)
        - Query: O(log n)
        - Update: O(log n)
    Space Complexity: O(n) for storing the tree
    """
    
    def __init__(self, data: List[Any], operation: callable = sum, 
                 default_value: Any = 0):
        """
        Initialize Segment Tree
        Args:
            data: Input array
            operation: Operation function (sum, min, max, etc.)
            default_value: Default value for empty segments
        """
        self.n = len(data)
        self.data = data
        self.operation = operation
        self.default_value = default_value
        
        # Calculate tree size
        self.size = 1
        while self.size < self.n:
            self.size *= 2
            
        # Initialize tree with default values
        self.tree = [default_value] * (2 * self.size)
        
        # Build the tree
        self._build()
    
    def _build(self) -> None:
        """Build the segment tree from input data"""
        # Fill leaves
        for i in range(self.n):
            self.tree[self.size + i] = self.data[i]
            
        # Build parents
        for i in range(self.size - 1, 0, -1):
            self.tree[i] = self.operation([self.tree[2 * i], self.tree[2 * i + 1]])
    
    def query(self, left: int, right: int) -> Any:
        """
        Query range [left, right]
        Time: O(log n), Space: O(1)
        """
        left += self.size
        right += self.size
        result = self.default_value
        
        while left <= right:
            if left % 2 == 1:
                result = self.operation([result, self.tree[left]])
                left += 1
            if right % 2 == 0:
                result = self.operation([result, self.tree[right]])
                right -= 1
                
            left //= 2
            right //= 2
            
        return result
    
    def update(self, index: int, value: Any) -> None:
        """
        Update value at index
        Time: O(log n), Space: O(1)
        """
        index += self.size
        self.tree[index] = value
        
        # Update parents
        index //= 2
        while index >= 1:
            self.tree[index] = self.operation([self.tree[2 * index], 
                                             self.tree[2 * index + 1]])
            index //= 2
    
    def range_update(self, left: int, right: int, value: Any) -> None:
        """
        Lazy range update (basic implementation)
        Time: O(n) worst-case, Space: O(1)
        """
        for i in range(left, right + 1):
            self.update(i, value)
    
    def get_array(self) -> List[Any]:
        """Get current array state"""
        return self.tree[self.size:self.size + self.n]

class TreeAnalyzer:
    """Analyzer for tree performance and characteristics"""
    
    @staticmethod
    def measure_performance(tree: TreeInterface, operations: int = 1000) -> Dict[str, float]:
        """Measure tree performance with random operations"""
        import time
        
        results = {}
        values = [random.randint(1, 10000) for _ in range(operations)]
        
        # Insertion performance
        start_time = time.time()
        for value in values:
            tree.insert(value)
        results['insert_time'] = time.time() - start_time
        
        # Search performance
        search_values = values[:operations//2] + [random.randint(1, 10000) for _ in range(operations//2)]
        start_time = time.time()
        for value in search_values:
            tree.search(value)
        results['search_time'] = time.time() - start_time
        
        # Deletion performance
        delete_values = values[:operations//2]
        start_time = time.time()
        for value in delete_values:
            tree.delete(value)
        results['delete_time'] = time.time() - start_time
        
        # Tree characteristics
        results['height'] = tree.get_height()
        results['size'] = tree.get_size()
        
        return results
    
    @staticmethod
    def compare_trees(trees: List[TreeInterface], operations: int = 1000) -> Dict[str, Dict[str, float]]:
        """Compare performance of multiple trees"""
        results = {}
        
        for i, tree in enumerate(trees):
            tree_name = tree.__class__.__name__
            results[tree_name] = TreeAnalyzer.measure_performance(tree, operations)
            
        return results

self._rotate_right(node) self.rotations_count += 1 # Right heavy elif node.balance_factor < -1: # Right-Left case if node.right and node.right.balance_factor > 0: node.right = ============================================================================= # B-TREE IMPLEMENTATION # ============================================================================= class BTreeNode: """Node class for B-Tree""" def __init__(self, t: int, leaf: bool = False): self.t = t # Minimum degree self.leaf = leaf self.keys: List[Any] = [] self.children: List['BTreeNode'] = [] self.n = 0 # Current number of keys def __str__(self): return f"BTreeNode(keys={self.keys}, leaf={self.leaf})" class BTree(TreeInterface): """ B-Tree Implementation (Balanced multi-way search tree) Time Complexity: - Insert: O(t * log_t n) - Search: O(t * log_t n) - Delete: O(t * log_t n) - Split: O(t) Space Complexity: O(n) for storing n keys """ def __init__(self, t: int = 3): """ Initialize B-Tree Args: t: Minimum degree (defines the range for number of keys) """ self.root: Optional[BTreeNode] = None self.t = t # Minimum degree self._size = 0 def insert(self, value: Any) -> bool: """Insert value into B-Tree - Time: O(t * log_t n), Space: O(t * log_t n)""" if self.root is None: self.root = BTreeNode(self.t, True) self.root.keys.append(value) self.root.n = 1 self._size += 1 return True # If root is full, then tree grows in height if self.root.n == 2 * self.t - 1: # Create new root new_root = BTreeNode(self.t, False) new_root.children.append(self.root) # Split the old root self._split_child(new_root, 0) # New root has two children now, decide which one will have new key i = 0 if new_root.keys[0] < value: i += 1 self._insert_non_full(new_root.children[i], value) self.root = new_root else: self._insert_non_full(self.root, value) self._size += 1 return True def _insert_non_full(self, node: BTreeNode, value: Any) -> None: """Insert into non-full node""" i = node.n - 1 if node.leaf: # Insert into leaf node node.keys.append(None) # Make space while i >= 0 and node.keys[i] > value: node.keys[i + 1] = node.keys[i] i -= 1 node.keys[i + 1] = value node.n += 1 else: # Find child which will have the new key while i >= 0 and node.keys[i] > value: i -= 1 i += 1 # Check if child is full if node.children[i].n == 2 * self.t - 1: self._split_child(node, i) # After split, the middle key of node.children[i] goes up if node.keys[i] < value: i += 1 self._insert_non_full(node.children[i], value) def _split_child(self, parent: BTreeNode, i: int) -> None: """Split the child node""" t = self.t y = parent.children[i] # Child to split z = BTreeNode(t, y.leaf) # Create new node z z.n = t - 1 # Copy the last (t-1) keys of y to z z.keys = y.keys[t:(2 * t - 1)] # Copy the last t children of y to z if not leaf if not y.leaf: z.children = y.children[t:(2 * t)] # Reduce number of keys in y y.n = t - 1 # Create space for new child in parent parent.children.insert(i + 1, z) # A key of y will move to parent parent.keys.insert(i, y.keys[t - 1]) # Update parent's key count parent.n += 1 def search(self, value: Any) -> bool: """Search for value in B-Tree - Time: O(t * log_t n), Space: O(log_t n)""" return self._search_recursive(self.root, value) is not None def _search_recursive(self, node: Optional[BTreeNode], value: Any) -> Optional[BTreeNode]: """Recursive search in B-Tree""" if node is None: return None i = 0 while i < node.n and value > node.keys[i]: i += 1 if i < node.n and value == node.keys[i]: return node if node.leaf: return None return self._search_recursive(node.children[i], value) def delete(self, value: Any) -> bool: """Delete value from B-Tree - Time: O(t * log_t n), Space: O(t * log_t n)""" if self.root is None: return False result = self._delete_recursive(self.root, value) if result: self._size -= 1 # If root has 0 keys, make its first child as new root if self.root.n == 0: if self.root.leaf: self.root = None else: self.root = self.root.children[0] return result def _delete_recursive(self, node: BTreeNode, value: Any) -> bool: """Recursive deletion from B-Tree""" idx = self._find_key_index(node, value) if idx < node.n and node.keys[idx] == value: # Key found in this node if node.leaf: self._remove_from_leaf(node, idx) else: self._remove_from_non_leaf(node, idx) return True else: if node.leaf: return False # Key not found # Key is in subtree rooted with this node flag = (idx == node.n) # True if last child # If child has less than t keys, fill it if node.children[idx].n < self.t: self._fill_child(node, idx) # If last child was merged, it must have merged with previous child if flag and idx > node.n: return self._delete_recursive(node.children[idx - 1], value) else: return self._delete_recursive(node.children[idx], value) def _find_key_index(self, node: BTreeNode, value: Any) -> int: """Find index of key in node""" idx = 0 while idx < node.n and node.keys[idx] < value: idx += 1 return idx def _remove_from_leaf(self, node: BTreeNode, idx: int) -> None: """Remove key from leaf node""" node.keys.pop(idx) node.n -= 1 def _remove_from_non_leaf(self, node: BTreeNode, idx: int) -> None: """Remove key from non-leaf node""" key = node.keys[idx] # If predecessor child has at least t keys if node.children[idx].n >= self.t: pred = self._get_predecessor(node, idx) node.keys[idx] = pred self._delete_recursive(node.children[idx], pred) # If successor child has at least t keys elif node.children[idx + 1].n >= self.t: succ = self._get_successor(node, idx) node.keys[idx] = succ self._delete_recursive(node.children[idx + 1], succ) # Both children have t-1 keys, merge them else: self._merge_children(node, idx) self._delete_recursive(node.children[idx], key) def _get_predecessor(self, node: BTreeNode, idx: int) -> Any: """Get predecessor of key at index idx""" current = node.children[idx] while not current.leaf: current = current.children[current.n] return current.keys[current.n - 1] def _get_successor(self, node: BTreeNode, idx: int) -> Any: """Get successor of key at index idx""" current = node.children[idx + 1] while not current.leaf: current = current.children[0] return current.keys[0] def _fill_child(self, parent: BTreeNode, idx: int) -> None: """Fill child that has less than t keys""" # Borrow from previous sibling if possible if idx != 0 and parent.children[idx - 1].n >= self.t: self._borrow_from_prev(parent, idx) # Borrow from next sibling if possible elif idx != parent.n and parent.children[idx + 1].n >= self.t: self._borrow_from_next(parent, idx) # Merge with sibling else: if idx != parent.n: self._merge_children(parent, idx) else: self._merge_children(parent, idx - 1) def _borrow_from_prev(self, parent: BTreeNode, idx: int) -> None: """Borrow key from previous child""" child = parent.children[idx] sibling = parent.children[idx - 1] # Move all keys in child one step ahead child.keys.insert(0, parent.keys[idx - 1]) child.n += 1 if not child.leaf: child.children.insert(0, sibling.children.pop()) # Move key from sibling to parent parent.keys[idx - 1] = sibling.keys.pop() sibling.n -= 1 def _borrow_from_next(self, parent: BTreeNode, idx: int) -> None: """Borrow key from next child""" child = parent.children[idx] sibling = parent.children[idx + 1] # Move key from parent to child child.keys.append(parent.keys[idx]) child.n += 1 if not child.leaf: child.children.append(sibling.children.pop(0)) # Move key from sibling to parent parent.keys[idx] = sibling.keys.pop(0) sibling.n -= 1 def _merge_children(self, parent: BTreeNode, idx: int) -> None: """Merge child[idx] with child[idx+1]""" child = parent.children[idx] sibling = parent.children[idx + 1] # Pull key from parent and insert into child child.keys.append(parent.keys.pop(idx)) child.n += 1 # Copy keys from sibling to child child.keys.extend(sibling.keys) child.n += sibling.n # Copy children from sibling to child if not leaf if not child.leaf: child.children.extend(sibling.children) # Remove sibling from parent parent.children.pop(idx + 1) parent.n -= 1 def get_height(self) -> int: """Get tree height - Time: O(log_t n), Space: O(1)""" if self.root is None: return 0 height = 0 current = self.root while not current.leaf: height += 1 current = current.children[0] return height + 1 def get_size(self) -> int: """Get number of keys - Time: O(1), Space: O(1)""" return self._size def traverse_inorder(self) -> List[Any]: """Inorder traversal - Time: O(n), Space: O(log_t n)""" result = [] if self.root: """
Advanced Tree Data Structures GUI Application
=============================================
Integrating DSA trees with real-world projects using Tkinter
"""

import tkinter as tk
from tkinter import ttk, messagebox, scrolledtext
import random
import time
from typing import Any, List, Optional, Tuple, Dict, Deque
from collections import deque
import json
from abc import ABC, abstractmethod

# =============================================================================
# TREE DATA STRUCTURES (From previous implementation)
# =============================================================================

class TreeInterface(ABC):
    @abstractmethod
    def insert(self, value: Any) -> bool: pass
    @abstractmethod
    def search(self, value: Any) -> bool: pass
    @abstractmethod
    def delete(self, value: Any) -> bool: pass
    @abstractmethod
    def get_height(self) -> int: pass
    @abstractmethod
    def get_size(self) -> int: pass
    @abstractmethod
    def traverse_inorder(self) -> List[Any]: pass
    @abstractmethod
    def traverse_preorder(self) -> List[Any]: pass
    @abstractmethod
    def traverse_postorder(self) -> List[Any]: pass
    @abstractmethod
    def find_min(self) -> Any: pass
    @abstractmethod
    def find_max(self) -> Any: pass

class BSTNode:
    def __init__(self, value: Any):
        self.value = value
        self.left: Optional['BSTNode'] = None
        self.right: Optional['BSTNode'] = None
        self.parent: Optional['BSTNode'] = None

class BinarySearchTree(TreeInterface):
    def __init__(self):
        self.root: Optional[BSTNode] = None
        self._size = 0
        
    def insert(self, value: Any) -> bool:
        if self.root is None:
            self.root = BSTNode(value)
            self._size += 1
            return True
        return self._insert_recursive(self.root, value)
    
    def _insert_recursive(self, node: BSTNode, value: Any) -> bool:
        if value == node.value:
            return False
        if value < node.value:
            if node.left is None:
                node.left = BSTNode(value)
                node.left.parent = node
                self._size += 1
                return True
            return self._insert_recursive(node.left, value)
        else:
            if node.right is None:
                node.right = BSTNode(value)
                node.right.parent = node
                self._size += 1
                return True
            return self._insert_recursive(node.right, value)
    
    def search(self, value: Any) -> bool:
        return self._search_recursive(self.root, value)
    
    def _search_recursive(self, node: Optional[BSTNode], value: Any) -> bool:
        if node is None: return False
        if value == node.value: return True
        return (self._search_recursive(node.left, value) if value < node.value 
                else self._search_recursive(node.right, value))
    
    def delete(self, value: Any) -> bool:
        node_to_delete = self._find_node(self.root, value)
        if node_to_delete is None: return False
        self._delete_node(node_to_delete)
        self._size -= 1
        return True
    
    def _find_node(self, node: Optional[BSTNode], value: Any) -> Optional[BSTNode]:
        if node is None: return None
        if value == node.value: return node
        return (self._find_node(node.left, value) if value < node.value 
                else self._find_node(node.right, value))
    
    def _delete_node(self, node: BSTNode):
        if node.left is None and node.right is None:
            self._transplant(node, None)
        elif node.left is None:
            self._transplant(node, node.right)
        elif node.right is None:
            self._transplant(node, node.left)
        else:
            successor = self._find_min_node(node.right)
            if successor.parent != node:
                self._transplant(successor, successor.right)
                successor.right = node.right
                successor.right.parent = successor
            self._transplant(node, successor)
            successor.left = node.left
            successor.left.parent = successor
    
    def _transplant(self, u: BSTNode, v: Optional[BSTNode]):
        if u.parent is None: self.root = v
        elif u == u.parent.left: u.parent.left = v
        else: u.parent.right = v
        if v: v.parent = u.parent
    
    def _find_min_node(self, node: BSTNode) -> BSTNode:
        while node.left: node = node.left
        return node
    
    def get_height(self) -> int:
        return self._calculate_height(self.root)
    
    def _calculate_height(self, node: Optional[BSTNode]) -> int:
        if node is None: return 0
        return 1 + max(self._calculate_height(node.left), 
                      self._calculate_height(node.right))
    
    def get_size(self) -> int: return self._size
    
    def traverse_inorder(self) -> List[Any]:
        result = []; self._inorder_recursive(self.root, result); return result
    
    def _inorder_recursive(self, node: Optional[BSTNode], result: List[Any]):
        if node:
            self._inorder_recursive(node.left, result)
            result.append(node.value)
            self._inorder_recursive(node.right, result)
    
    def traverse_preorder(self) -> List[Any]:
        result = []; self._preorder_recursive(self.root, result); return result
    
    def _preorder_recursive(self, node: Optional[BSTNode], result: List[Any]):
        if node:
            result.append(node.value)
            self._preorder_recursive(node.left, result)
            self._preorder_recursive(node.right, result)
    
    def traverse_postorder(self) -> List[Any]:
        result = []; self._postorder_recursive(self.root, result); return result
    
    def _postorder_recursive(self, node: Optional[BSTNode], result: List[Any]):
        if node:
            self._postorder_recursive(node.left, result)
            self._postorder_recursive(node.right, result)
            result.append(node.value)
    
    def find_min(self) -> Any:
        if self.root is None: return None
        current = self.root
        while current.left: current = current.left
        return current.value
    
    def find_max(self) -> Any:
        if self.root is None: return None
        current = self.root
        while current.right: current = current.right
        return current.value

class AVLNode:
    def __init__(self, value: Any):
        self.value = value
        self.left: Optional['AVLNode'] = None
        self.right: Optional['AVLNode'] = None
        self.height = 1

class AVLTree(TreeInterface):
    def __init__(self):
        self.root: Optional[AVLNode] = None
        self._size = 0
        
    def insert(self, value: Any) -> bool:
        if self.root is None:
            self.root = AVLNode(value)
            self._size += 1
            return True
        self.root, inserted = self._insert_recursive(self.root, value)
        if inserted: self._size += 1
        return inserted
    
    def _insert_recursive(self, node: AVLNode, value: Any) -> Tuple[AVLNode, bool]:
        if value == node.value: return node, False
        if value < node.value:
            if node.left is None:
                node.left = AVLNode(value)
            else:
                node.left, inserted = self._insert_recursive(node.left, value)
                if not inserted: return node, False
        else:
            if node.right is None:
                node.right = AVLNode(value)
            else:
                node.right, inserted = self._insert_recursive(node.right, value)
                if not inserted: return node, False
        self._update_height(node)
        return self._balance_node(node), True
    
    def _update_height(self, node: AVLNode):
        left_h = node.left.height if node.left else 0
        right_h = node.right.height if node.right else 0
        node.height = 1 + max(left_h, right_h)
    
    def _balance_node(self, node: AVLNode) -> AVLNode:
        balance = self._get_balance(node)
        if balance > 1:
            if self._get_balance(node.left) < 0:
                node.left = self._rotate_left(node.left)
            return self._rotate_right(node)
        if balance < -1:
            if self._get_balance(node.right) > 0:
                node.right = self._rotate_right(node.right)
            return self._rotate_left(node)
        return node
    
    def _get_balance(self, node: AVLNode) -> int:
        left_h = node.left.height if node.left else 0
        right_h = node.right.height if node.right else 0
        return left_h - right_h
    
    def _rotate_left(self, z: AVLNode) -> AVLNode:
        y = z.right
        T2 = y.left
        y.left = z
        z.right = T2
        self._update_height(z)
        self._update_height(y)
        return y
    
    def _rotate_right(self, z: AVLNode) -> AVLNode:
        y = z.left
        T3 = y.right
        y.right = z
        z.left = T3
        self._update_height(z)
        self._update_height(y)
        return y
    
    def search(self, value: Any) -> bool:
        return self._search_recursive(self.root, value)
    
    def _search_recursive(self, node: Optional[AVLNode], value: Any) -> bool:
        if node is None: return False
        if value == node.value: return True
        return (self._search_recursive(node.left, value) if value < node.value 
                else self._search_recursive(node.right, value))
    
    def delete(self, value: Any) -> bool:
        if self.root is None: return False
        self.root, deleted = self._delete_recursive(self.root, value)
        if deleted: self._size -= 1
        return deleted
    
    def _delete_recursive(self, node: AVLNode, value: Any) -> Tuple[Optional[AVLNode], bool]:
        if value < node.value:
            if node.left is None: return node, False
            node.left, deleted = self._delete_recursive(node.left, value)
            if not deleted: return node, False
        elif value > node.value:
            if node.right is None: return node, False
            node.right, deleted = self._delete_recursive(node.right, value)
            if not deleted: return node, False
        else:
            if node.left is None: return node.right, True
            elif node.right is None: return node.left, True
            temp = self._find_min_node(node.right)
            node.value = temp.value
            node.right, _ = self._delete_recursive(node.right, temp.value)
            deleted = True
        self._update_height(node)
        return self._balance_node(node), True
    
    def _find_min_node(self, node: AVLNode) -> AVLNode:
        while node.left: node = node.left
        return node
    
    def get_height(self) -> int:
        return self.root.height if self.root else 0
    
    def get_size(self) -> int: return self._size
    
    def traverse_inorder(self) -> List[Any]:
        result = []; self._inorder_recursive(self.root, result); return result
    
    def _inorder_recursive(self, node: Optional[AVLNode], result: List[Any]):
        if node:
            self._inorder_recursive(node.left, result)
            result.append(node.value)
            self._inorder_recursive(node.right, result)
    
    def traverse_preorder(self) -> List[Any]:
        result = []; self._preorder_recursive(self.root, result); return result
    
    def _preorder_recursive(self, node: Optional[AVLNode], result: List[Any]):
        if node:
            result.append(node.value)
            self._preorder_recursive(node.left, result)
            self._preorder_recursive(node.right, result)
    
    def traverse_postorder(self) -> List[Any]:
        result = []; self._postorder_recursive(self.root, result); return result
    
    def _postorder_recursive(self, node: Optional[AVLNode], result: List[Any]):
        if node:
            self._postorder_recursive(node.left, result)
            self._postorder_recursive(node.right, result)
            result.append(node.value)
    
    def find_min(self) -> Any:
        if self.root is None: return None
        current = self.root
        while current.left: current = current.left
        return current.value
    
    def find_max(self) -> Any:
        if self.root is None: return None
        current = self.root
        while current.right: current = current.right
        return current.value
